DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "contextFraction.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

##############################################################
#
#  Setup
#
#

$a1 = random(2,5,1);
$b1 = random(2,5,1);
$c1 = random(1,4,5);
$x1 = Real(random(1,5,1));
$c2 = $c1*$x1;
$y1 = $c1 - $a1*$x1 - $b1;

Context('Fraction');
$deriv = Fraction(
	-(2*$a1*$x1 + $b1 + $y1),
	$x1
);

##############################################################
#
#  Text
#
#

BEGIN_TEXT
If \( $a1 x^2 + $b1 x + xy = $c2  \) and \( y($x1) = $y1 \),
find \( y'($x1) \) by implicit differentiation.
$BR $BR
\( y'($x1) = \) \{ ans_rule(5) \}
$BR
END_TEXT

##############################################################
#
#  Answers
#
#

ANS($deriv->cmp);

$a12 = 2*$a1;
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_SOLUTION
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR 
We differentiate both sides of the equation with respect to \(x\):
 \[ \frac{d}{dx} ($a1 x^2 + $b1 x + xy)=\frac{d}{dx}( $c2) \]
 \[ $a12 x + $b1 + x \frac{dy}{dx} + y = 0 \]
Solving for \( \frac{dy}{dx} \) gives
\[ \frac{dy}{dx} = -$a12 - \frac{$b1}{x} - \frac{y}{x} \]
Substituting  \( x = $x1 \) and \(y = $y1 \), we get
\[ \frac{dy}{dx} = $deriv \]

END_SOLUTION
;

